<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - CATERPILLAR C-10, C-12 AND 3406E ENGINES -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Throttle Position Sensor (TPS)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Throttle Position Sensor (TPS)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) and Circuits</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0821607" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.38in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect TPS from cab harness at conn. (404). At TPS side of (404) measure
                                    resistance to gnd. at terminals A, B and C (red, black and white wires).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404), A, B, and C to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the throttle position sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (400) from ECM. At (404) measure resistance between terminals A,
                                    B and C (circuits 99E, 99-G and 99). There should be no continuity between the three
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404) between 99E, 99-G and 99.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short circuit, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 (circuit 97-G) to gnd. At
                                    conn. (404) and terminal B (circuit 99-GA) measure resistance to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404), 99-GA to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99-GA path to ground, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 to 37 (circuit 97-G to 99). At
                                    connector (404) measure resistance between terminals B and C (circuit 99-GA to 99).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404), 99-GA to 99.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99 between connectors (404) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 to 35 (circuit 97-G to 99E).
                                    At conn. (404) measure resistance between terminals B and A (circuit 99-GA and 99E).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404), 99-GA to 99E.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99E between connectors (404) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect (400) at ECM. Turn ignition on. At conn. (404) measure voltage between
                                    terminals A and B (circuit 99E and 99-GA).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404), 99E to 99-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>8 &#177; 0.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Have Caterpillar dealer diagnose the ECM.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the throttle position sensor and reconnect connectors. Test system
                                    operation and note if defect is still present. TPS works OK?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>End test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Have Caterpillar dealer diagnose the ECM.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
